just had a baby think i have obessessive compulsive disorder help please i have kids and just had another baby weeks ago after my second was born i started developing thoughts and images of hurting others and sometimes myself i would never act on them though they are just images in my head that wont go away i also find myself counting things over and over making sure things are in right order afraid of burglars house fire killers etc i used to act soo normal all of a sudden these have occured now for a year wondering can my ob gyn prescribe me antidepressants or will he send me to someone else what should i tell him im afraid of talking bout this and need to know what to say so it wont sound like im a crazy person will meds take my syptoms away and make me normal again sorry so long but please take this to heart because i really really feel for women who go through post partum depression because i went through it horribly what it sounds like is panic disorder typical post pregnancy horomone changes just because you have panic disorder doesn't mean you'll have a panic attack there is no shame in this and please do not let anyone dismiss you you mentioned feelings of hurting others and yourself though you know you won't really do it this is a way for your brain to put off things off what i mean by this is that your have a ton of stress going on you're a mommy of three you have a home to care for you have bills to think of you might have a relationship your dealing with all of this adds up and it has to go somewhere so you're brain thinks of the worst thing it can so you can avoid thinking of all the real life stress you have when you get your scary thoughts think to yourself what's really bothering me and how can i get help to handle this also it helps to say to yourself these are thoughts and just thoughts i'm a good person who can handle whatever is thrown at me can a friend or family member help you so you don't have so much on your plate can you put off some things like a load of laundry or things that really don't have to be done an anti depressant can help and if you need to go on a mild you most certainly should but you have to teach yourself how to handle your feelings you are not crazy you are not a bad person you are a good mother as hard as it is try to take a few minutes a day to yourself and relax lay on your bed and close your eyes breath deep and think of a calming blue sky just repeat that it's just stress and it's ok you are entitled to feel stress breath in through your nose and out your mouth i could go on and on but look up some things on panic disorder because there is a lot of information online this can help you i do recomend midwest stress center i went through therapy pills all kinds of things but the stress center was what helped me get over the same thing you're going through good luck Panic attack Anxiety Clinical depression Obsessive-compulsive disorder Stuttering Bipolar disorder Post-traumatic stress disorder Borderline personality disorder Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Insomnia Charles Darwin's illness Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sigmund Freud Urinary incontinence Autism Transactional analysis Friends Traumatic brain injury Theory of conduct EastEnders Breastfeeding Diving Social rule Jon Secada Anorexia nervosa Milton H. Erickson Cephalic disorder Meditation Medicine Dyslexia Postpartum depression Migraine The Ashlee Simpson Show Diazepam Out-of-body experience Chronic fatigue syndrome Psychoanalysis Agoraphobia Asperger syndrome About a Boy Columbine High School massacre Narcolepsy Sleep apnea Multiple sclerosis Antidepressant Schizophrenia Procrastination Haloperidol Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Stroke Humphrey Bogart Asthma Cognitive therapy Cerebral palsy Hearing impairment Infantilism 2000 Australian Grand Prix Binge eating disorder Piccolo Junior Saga Dog training Psoriasis Kill Bill Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Drowning Futurama (TV